Perhaps as much as 90% of the discussions and commentaries in the business media is redundant/reptitive. Maybe more... Watching the same "group stink" over and over again is painful. Many shows should return to their roots when deeper discussions prevailed.

"Group stink" is alive and well this week. The markets go up - talking heads are bullish. The markets go down - talking heads are bearish. As Lee Cooperman said yesterday on CNBC - buying high and selling low never made serious money.

Talking head in biz tv says the silver lining in the trade announcement is that more rate declines are coming. That is like saying the emergence of the housing crisis was good in 2007, because it led to lower interest rates. Jeez Louise

@realmoney Trading Alert.. I sold my entire VXX position at $24.65 just now - this was a very large long position and I recorded a sizeable gain. I am doing this as a reflection that this ETF is a trading sardine and not an eating sardine. @jimcramer @tomkeene

The TV business media is so disadvantaged to Twitter and other real time venues. Case in point, a huge announcement of China trade tariffs is made, yet the script isn't changed to conform to the breaking news. Much like newspapers....
